3. NONCOMMERCIAL USE ONLY

The Software and any Modified Version may not be used for Commercial Use
without separate written permission from the Licensor.

Prohibited Commercial Use includes, but is not limited to:

a. Selling the Software or a Modified Version.

b. Selling licenses, access, downloads, builds, or copies of the Software or a
   Modified Version.

c. Including the Software or a Modified Version as part of a paid product,
   service, subscription, or commercial package.

d. Providing paid hosting or cloud services primarily based on the Software.

e. Using the Software or a Modified Version primarily to generate commercial
   revenue.

f. Selling modifications, features, plugins, distributions, or services that
   substantially incorporate or depend upon the Software.

g. Using the Software as part of a proprietary commercial product without
   separate written permission from the Licensor.

Noncommercial donations and sponsorships are permitted only when they do not
provide exclusive software features, paid access, commercial licenses, or
other direct commercial benefits relating to the Software.

When there is uncertainty about whether a particular use constitutes
Commercial Use, written permission from the Licensor must be obtained before
such use.


4. PRIVATE MODIFICATION

You may privately modify the Software and store such modifications in private
repositories for personal and noncommercial development.

You are not required to publicly disclose a Modified Version that is used
solely by You and is not Distributed to any third party.

Once a Modified Version is Distributed to any third party, the source
availability requirements in Section 5 apply.

This means that private development is permitted, but closed-source
Distribution is not permitted.


5. SOURCE CODE REQUIREMENT FOR DISTRIBUTION

If You Distribute a Modified Version of the Software to any third party, You
must make the complete Corresponding Source of that exact distributed version
publicly available.

The Corresponding Source must:

a. Be publicly accessible without requiring individual approval or special
   permission.

b. Be available without payment.

c. Include all modifications made to the original Software.

d. Include the source code reasonably necessary to build and reproduce the
   distributed version.

e. Clearly identify that the Software has been modified.

f. Retain all applicable copyright notices.

g. Include an unmodified copy of this License.

The Corresponding Source must remain publicly available for as long as the
Modified Version continues to be publicly Distributed by You.

Distribution of binaries, executables, compiled packages, installers, or other
non-source forms of a Modified Version without providing the Corresponding
Source as required by this section is prohibited.


6. NO CLOSED-SOURCE DISTRIBUTION

You may not Distribute a Modified Version of the Software as closed-source or
proprietary software.

You may not impose legal terms, access restrictions, or technical measures
that prevent recipients from accessing the Corresponding Source required under
Section 5.

You may not use a private repository as the sole source-code location for a
Modified Version that has been Distributed to third parties.

A publicly Distributed Modified Version must have its Corresponding Source
available in a publicly accessible source repository or equivalent public
location.


